      <title>世界经济断层线从价格转向政治和债务</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-20/world-economy-fault-lines-shift-from-prices-to-politics-and-debt</link>
      <description><![CDATA[全球经济即将迎来意想不到的利好，通胀放缓为不太可能的软着陆铺平了道路。然而，尽管经济方面正在好转，但政治障碍依然存在。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-20/world-economy-fault-lines-shift-from-prices-to-politics-and-debt</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 20 Oct 2024 17:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>哈里斯称激烈竞争不仅仅关乎个性</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-20/harris-says-tight-race-must-be-about-more-than-personalities</link>
      <description><![CDATA[副总统卡马拉·哈里斯敦促亚特兰大地区的教会信徒拒绝那些散布仇恨和分裂情绪的候选人，试图在 11 月 5 日大选前的最后冲刺中动员黑人选民。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-10-20/harris-says-tight-race-must-be-about-more-than-personalities</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 20 Oct 2024 16:09:46 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
